Implementation details for P5.2 - Expired Plan Cleanup:

## Architecture Decisions
- Background goroutine with configurable interval (default: 1 hour)
- Graceful deletion - no error if plan doesn't exist
- Callback mechanism for external notification systems
- Stats tracking for observability

## Store Methods Added
- DeletePlan(id string) error - removes single plan file
- DeleteExpiredPlans() (int, error) - scans and deletes expired

## CleanupService API
- NewCleanupService(store, config) - constructor
- Start(ctx) / Stop() - lifecycle management
- CleanupNow() - on-demand cleanup
- IsRunning() / Stats() - introspection

## Spec Compliance
- deployment-state.md:146-150 - Expired plans deleted ✅
- Plans expire 24h after creation if not approved
- Hourly check interval (configurable)

## Testing Coverage
- 11 new tests for cleanup functionality
- Lifecycle tests (start/stop/double operations)
- Expired vs valid plan handling
- Callback invocation verification
- Statistics tracking

## Integration Points
- Can be started in main.go alongside server
- OnCleanup callback for logging/alerting
- CleanupStats can be exposed via MCP resource
